{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Anomaly Detection using Machine Learning (All Machines)
",
    "
",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to use an unsupervised machine learning model to detect anomalies in the sensor data from the `AIM_MonitoringSystem.xlsx` file, applied across all available machines."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup
",
    "
",
    "Import the necessary libraries. We'll use `pandas` for data manipulation, `scikit-learn` for the anomaly detection model, and `matplotlib` for plotting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd
",
    "import numpy as np
",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest
",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
",
    "
",
    "print("Libraries imported successfully.")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load Data
",
    "
",
    "Load the `SensorData` sheet from the Excel file. This sheet contains the time-series data for all sensors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:
",
    "    xls = pd.ExcelFile('AIM_MonitoringSystem.xlsx')
",
    "    sensor_df = pd.read_excel(xls, 'SensorData')
",
    "    print("SensorData loaded successfully.")
",
    "    display(sensor_df.head())
",
    "except FileNotFoundError:
",
    "    print("Error: AIM_MonitoringSystem.xlsx not found. Make sure the file is in the same directory as this notebook.")
",
    "    sensor_df = pd.DataFrame() # Create an empty DataFrame to avoid errors later"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Preprocess Data for All Machines
",
    "
",
    "We will preprocess data for each machine separately. For each machine, we will:
",
    "1. Convert the `Timestamp` column to a proper datetime format.
",
    "2. Pivot the table so that each sensor (`SensorID`) becomes a column.
",
    "3. Handle any missing values that may appear after pivoting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "processed_data = {}
",
    "
",
    "if not sensor_df.empty:
",
    "    sensor_df['Timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(sensor_df['Timestamp'])
",
    "    unique_machines = sensor_df['Machine'].unique()
",
    "
",
    "    for machine in unique_machines:
",
    "        print(f"
Processing data for machine: {machine}")
",
    "        machine_df = sensor_df[sensor_df['Machine'] == machine].copy()
",
    "
",
    "        if not machine_df.empty:
",
    "            machine_pivot = machine_df.pivot_table(index='Timestamp', columns='SensorID', values='Value')
",
    "            machine_pivot.fillna(method='ffill', inplace=True)
",
    "            machine_pivot.fillna(method='bfill', inplace=True)
",
    "            machine_pivot.fillna(0, inplace=True) # Fill any remaining NaNs, e.g., at the very start
",
    "
",
    "            if not machine_pivot.empty and not machine_pivot.isnull().values.all() and len(machine_pivot.columns) > 0:
",
    "                processed_data[machine] = machine_pivot
",
    "                print(f"Data preprocessed for {machine}.")
",
    "                display(machine_pivot.head())
",
    "            else:
",
    "                print(f"Warning: No valid data after preprocessing for {machine}. Skipping anomaly detection for this machine.")
",
    "        else:
",
    "            print(f"No data found for machine {machine}.")
",
    "else:
",
    "    print("Sensor DataFrame is empty. Cannot preprocess data for any machine.")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Train Anomaly Detection Model for All Machines
",
    "
",
    "We will apply the **Isolation Forest** algorithm to each machine's preprocessed data to detect anomalies."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if processed_data:
",
    "    for machine, data in processed_data.items():
",
    "        print(f"
Training anomaly detection model for machine: {machine}")
",
    "        if not data.empty and len(data.columns) > 0:
",
    "            model = IsolationForest(contamination=0.05, random_state=42)
",
    "            model.fit(data)
",
    "            data['anomaly'] = model.predict(data[data.columns])
",
    "            processed_data[machine] = data # Update the dictionary with the new 'anomaly' column
",
    "            print(f"Anomaly detection complete for {machine}.")
",
    "            display(data.head())
",
    "        else:
",
    "            print(f"Skipping {machine}: No valid data for model training.")
",
    "else:
",
    "    print("No processed data available for any machine to train models.")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Visualize Anomalies for All Machines
",
    "
",
    "We will visualize the detected anomalies for each machine, plotting a representative sensor and then all sensors in subplots."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if processed_data:
",
    "    for machine, data in processed_data.items():
",
    "        print(f"
Visualizing anomalies for machine: {machine}")
",
    "        if not data.empty and 'anomaly' in data.columns:
",
    "            anomalies = data[data['anomaly'] == -1]
",
    "
",
    "            # Plot for a specific sensor (first available sensor for this machine)
",
    "            sensor_cols = [col for col in data.columns if col != 'anomaly']
",
    "            if sensor_cols:
",
    "                sensor_to_plot = sensor_cols[0] # Pick the first sensor for this machine
",
    "                plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
",
    "                plt.plot(data.index, data[sensor_to_plot], label='Normal')
",
    "                if not anomalies.empty:
",
    "                    anomalies_for_sensor = anomalies[anomalies[sensor_to_plot].notna()]
",
    "                    if not anomalies_for_sensor.empty:
",
    "                        plt.scatter(anomalies_for_sensor.index, anomalies_for_sensor[sensor_to_plot], color='red', label='Anomaly')
",
    "                plt.title(f'Anomaly Detection for {sensor_to_plot} on {machine}')
",
    "                plt.xlabel('Timestamp')
",
    "                plt.ylabel('Sensor Value')
",
    "                plt.legend()
",
    "                plt.grid(True)
",
    "                plt.show()
",
    "            else:
",
    "                print(f"No sensor columns found for {machine} to plot a specific sensor.")
",
    "
",
    "            # Plot for all sensors
",
    "            num_sensors = len(sensor_cols)
",
    "            if num_sensors > 0:
",
    "                fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_sensors, 1, figsize=(15, num_sensors * 3), sharex=True)
",
    "                if num_sensors == 1:
",
    "                    axes = [axes] # Ensure axes is iterable
",
    "
",
    "                for ax, sensor in zip(axes, sensor_cols):
",
    "                    ax.plot(data.index, data[sensor], label='Normal')
",
    "                    if not anomalies.empty:
",
    "                        anomalies_for_sensor = anomalies[anomalies[sensor].notna()]
",
    "                        if not anomalies_for_sensor.empty:
",
    "                            ax.scatter(anomalies_for_sensor.index, anomalies_for_sensor[sensor], color='red', label='Anomaly')
",
    "                    ax.set_title(f'{sensor} on {machine}')
",
    "                    ax.legend()
",
    "                    ax.grid(True)
",
    "
",
    "                plt.xlabel('Timestamp')
",
    "                fig.suptitle(f'All Sensor Anomaly Detection for {machine}', y=1.02, fontsize=16) # Add main title
",
    "                fig.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.98]) # Adjust layout for suptitle
",
    "                plt.show()
",
    "            else:
",
    "                print(f"No sensor columns found for {machine} to plot all sensors.")
",
    "        else:
",
    "            print(f"Skipping visualization for {machine}: Data is empty or 'anomaly' column is missing.")
",
    "else:
",
    "    print("No processed data available for any machine to visualize.")"
   ]
  }
 ],
